HEADWORD: Copyholder
<hw>Cop"y*hold`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Eng. Law)</fld> <def>One possessed of land in copyhold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(print.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A device for
holding copy for a compositor.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One who reads
copy to a proof reader.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Copying</ent>⟦br⟧
